                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756.94/85b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-13T03:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1940—3 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>149. Consul General at Batavia has telegraphed<note n="32" xml:id="d19fn32"
                        >Telegram May 12, 11 p.m.; not printed.</note> that twice today station KGEI
                    at San Francisco announced that French marines had landed in the Netherlands
                    East Indies. We have requested the manager of the station to announce that no
                    allied forces have landed in the Netherlands East Indies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
